# [MISER=8] Missing Viz Block JS — 4 files

Four JS files are missing. Demo data and CSS already exist for each. Write JS only.

All blocks must:
- Use `import.meta.url` to build demo JSON fallback URL: `new URL('./blockname-demo.json', import.meta.url).href`
- Show a visible empty state `<div class="viz-empty-state">` when no data/content
- Three.js blocks: use `loadScript` from `../../scripts/aem.js`, then `const THREE = window.THREE`

---

## Phase 1 (parallel): Write the 4 missing JS files

### Step 1a: viz-pipeline.js

Target: `blocks/viz-pipeline/viz-pipeline.js`

Write a full block JS for an AEM→CDN pipeline monitor. Reads demo data from
`blocks/viz-pipeline/viz-pipeline-demo.json` (has nodes[] and edges[] with lat/lon, type,
status, label fields). Renders as an animated SVG/canvas force-directed graph with:
- Nodes as labeled boxes colored by `type` (cdn=blue, origin=orange, cache=purple, edge=green)
- Edges as animated lines showing `rps` traffic flow with arrow direction
- Status `"error"` nodes pulsing red
- Click node → side panel shows metrics (rps, p99Ms, errorPct)
- Empty state when no data

CSS is at `blocks/viz-pipeline/viz-pipeline.css` — use its custom properties (`--vp-*`).
Do NOT use Three.js — use SVG or Canvas2D only.

### Step 1b: viz-office-map.js

Target: `blocks/viz-office-map/viz-office-map.js`

Write a floor map block. Reads demo data from `blocks/viz-office-map/viz-office-map-demo.json`
(has zones[] with id, label, type, x, y, w, h (0-1 normalized), occupied, capacity fields).
Renders as a canvas floor plan:
- Zones as colored rectangles (meeting=blue, open-plan=green, amenity=gray)
- Fill opacity based on `occupied/capacity` ratio (0%=dim, 100%=bright)
- Label + "12/20" occupancy text in each zone
- Auto-refreshes every 30s (re-fetches demo JSON with jitter to simulate live changes)
- Hover tooltip with zone name and full occupancy details
- Empty state when no data

CSS is at `blocks/viz-office-map/viz-office-map.css`.

### Step 1c: viz-secure-feed.js

Target: `blocks/viz-secure-feed/viz-secure-feed.js`

Write a block that demonstrates the authenticated-source-to-EDS pattern. Reads from
`blocks/viz-secure-feed/viz-secure-feed-demo.json` (has feedTitle, syncedAt, source,
metrics[] with label/value/delta/trend, note fields).
Renders as a dark card:
- Title bar with lock icon + feedTitle
- "Synced: <syncedAt>" timestamp + source label
- Grid of metric tiles: label, value in large text, delta badge (▲/▼) colored green/red
- Italic note at bottom
- No live polling — just display the static JSON (simulates "data pushed by AEM sync job")
- Empty state when no data

CSS is at `blocks/viz-secure-feed/viz-secure-feed.css`.

### Step 1d: m3d-photo-globe.js

Target: `blocks/m3d-photo-globe/m3d-photo-globe.js`

Write a Three.js photo globe. Reads block row 0 as a DAM folder path (or falls back to
empty state with instructions). Since we can't actually fetch DAM in demo, render a demo
globe using 8 placeholder photos from `https://picsum.photos/seed/{n}/400/300` at
hard-coded lat/lon positions.

Use Three.js (`loadScript` from `../../scripts/aem.js`, then `window.THREE`).
- IcosahedronGeometry for the globe, MeshBasicMaterial with a canvas-drawn ocean/land texture
- Each photo: load as a Sprite (SpriteMaterial with THREE.TextureLoader), position at lat/lon
  using standard spherical coords `(radius * cos(lat) * sin(lon), radius * sin(lat), radius * cos(lat) * cos(lon))`
- Click a sprite → pause rotation, show lightbox overlay with full image + close button
- Drag to rotate (mouse orbit)
- Height from row 2 (default 480)
- Empty state: "Choose a DAM folder in the block to load photos"

CSS is at `blocks/m3d-photo-globe/m3d-photo-globe.css`.

